<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Devastated Lisa Curry has shared a heartbreaking plea to her friends and family, just days after burying her eldest daughter Jaimi Kenny. </p>

<p>Posting to Instagram on Tuesday, the Olympic swimmer shared a throwback photo of herself tenderly hugging Jamie - who died at the age of 33 last Monday after battling alcoholism and an eating disorder for years.  </p>

<p>In a gut-wrenching caption, Lisa wrote: 'I don’t know what to do.....', alongside emojis depicting a sad face, an a broken heart and an angel. </p>

<p>'I don't know what to do': Grief-stricken Lisa Curry penned a heartbreaking plea via Instagram on Tuesday, just days after burying her eldest daughter Jaimi Kenny </p>

<p>Lisa's post was quickly flooded with condolences from her army of followers. </p>

<p>For free and confidential support, contact Lifeline on 13 11 14, or the Butterfly Foundation for eating disorder concerns on 1800 ED HOPE    </p>
